<Note>
<Para>GDS administration program capabilities preceded by a pound sign (#)
are processed directly by the GDS administration program.  These entries
are described later in this section.
</Para>
</Note>
<Para>For redefinition of a terminal capability you have to edit the
<Literal>adm_term_cap</Literal> file.  Replace the names of termcap capabilities
that are undefined in your specific machine/terminal configuration by
valid ones.  For example, if <Literal>ya</Literal> is not defined but <Literal>k2</Literal> is, it
could be replaced by <Literal>k2</Literal>.  Function key <Literal>F2</Literal> would then act as
the <Literal>&lt;Menu&gt;</Literal> key.
</Para>
<Para>The exact format of <Literal>adm_term_cap</Literal> is described in the file itself.
</Para>
