<Sect1 Id="OSFGDS.GDSOAT.div.18">
<Title>Administration of GDS By Using Input Files</Title>
<IndexTerm Id="OSFGDS.GDSOAT.indx.31">
<Primary>Global Directory Service (GDS)</Primary>
<Secondary>batch mode administration</Secondary>
</IndexTerm>
<Para>The GDS commands, <Command>gdsditadm</Command> and <Command>gdscacheadm</Command>,
accept ASCII input files that can automate specific administration
procedures.  Input files must provide mask entries in the
same mask sequence as an administrator would provide interactively.
</Para>
<Para>Every input in a mask field must be entered in a separate line in the
input file.  The end-of-line character is interpreted as a key input.
</Para>
<Para>Any space that remains following a value in an input field must be filled
with underscores so that longer values specified beforehand for the
same field will be overwritten correctly.
</Para>
<Para>Comments that begin with <Literal>:*</Literal> (colon asterisk)
and end with <Literal>*:</Literal> (asterisk, colon) are transferred from
the input file to the output file.
Comments must be enclosed between : colons.
</Para>
